class ai_flow.test.store.test_mongo_store.TestMongoDB(methodName='runTest')[source]¶

Bases: ai_flow.test.store.common.AbstractTestStore, unittest.case.TestCase

Run tests against a MongoDB database. Run the test command with the environment variables set, e.g: MONGODB_TEST_USERNAME=your_username MONGODB_TEST_PASSWORD=your_password <your-test-command>. You may optionally specify MONGODB host via MONGODB_TEST_HOST and specify MONGODB port via MONGODB_TEST_PORT.

Create an instance of the class that will use the named test method when executed. Raises a ValueError if the instance does not have a method with the specified name.

class ai_flow.test.store.test_sqlalchemy_store.TestSqlAlchemyStoreMySQL(methodName='runTest')[source]¶

Bases: ai_flow.test.store.common.AbstractTestStore, unittest.case.TestCase

Run tests against a MySQL database. Run the test command with the environment variables set, e.g: MYSQL_TEST_USERNAME=your_username MYSQL_TEST_PASSWORD=your_password <your-test-command>. You may optionally specify MySQL host via MYSQL_TEST_HOST (default is 100.69.96.145) and specify MySQL port via MYSQL_TEST_PORT (default is 3306).
